[{"id":"VR021843","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div>Which of the following can be inferred from the diagram above that shows the dependence of potential energy on the internuclear distance between two atoms?</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n","rubricRef":"VR021843_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a graph of a curve. The horizontal axis is labeled “Internuclear Distance, in picometers,” and the numbers 0 through 250, in increments of 50, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Potential Energy, in kilojoules per mole,” and the numbers negative 500 through positive 400, in increments of 100, are indicated. A dashed horizontal line extends from the vertical axis at 0 kilojoules per mole. The data represented in the graph are as follows. Note that all values are approximate. The curve begins at the point representing 25 picometers, 400 kilojoules per mole, and moves steeply downward and to the right until it reaches a minimum at the point representing 75 picometers, negative 430 kilojoules per mole. It then moves steeply upward and to the right, and then becomes less steep. The curve approaches the dashed horizontal line at 0 kilojoules per mole from the bottom, but does not touch it.\" height=\"233\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR021843.g01.png\" width=\"300\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The atoms form a bond with a bond length of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"25 picometers\"><math alttext=\"25 picometers\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>25</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.3em\"></mspace><mtext>pm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The atoms form a bond with a bond length of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"75 picometers\">